title.narrative: Project to Support a Rural Economic Development Program

description.narrative: The Project Development Objectives (PDO) are (i) to improve the competitiveness of rural productive supply chains with strong indigenous participation; and (ii) to strengthen the institutional capacity of the public entities participating in the program through the adoption of a territorial management model with indigenous participation.

title.narrative: At least 200 new productive supply chain partnerships reaching at least 30,000 project beneficiaries are operating (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Original target of 300 partnerships was revised down to 200; Number of beneficiaries was also revised down from 45,000 to 30,000,where at least 12,000 are direct and 18,000 are indirect beneficiaries; revised through restructuring in March 2013

13 have been canceled;Direct beneficiaries (17,990) + indirect beneficiaries (89,950) = 107,940 beneficiaries from productivepartnershipsThere are additional 11,316 direct and indirect beneficiaries from business strengthening activities under the project

title.narrative: Preparation of half-yearly project monitoring reports within 45 days of the end of each semester and a coordinated annual project plan at least 3 months prior to the beginning of the fiscal year

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved. Revised through restructuring in March 2013
2 per year

title.narrative: 90% of all municipalities covered by the project have a territorial management plan (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved and exceeded. Revised through restructuring in March 2013
90% corresponds to 300; now these exist for 328 municipalities, which is equivalent to 98%

title.narrative: 100% of infrastructure investments have a maintenance plan signed by the beneficiaries (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: TTarget has been achieved; Revised through restructuring in March 2013
Notifications of receipt of those plans are in the project archives

title.narrative: The decentralized strategic territorial information management system is operational in 3 departments, and provides service coverage to the remaining departments (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved and surpassed. Revised through restructuring in March 2013
Operational in 8 departments

title.narrative: 100% of the beneficiaries of the improvement in rural roads have access during the whole year to critical markets (revised indicators)

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved; Revised through restructuring in March 2013
Public access for completed bridges

title.narrative: 100% of the productive infrastruture approved by the Investment Coordination Committee (ICC) is implemented according to timing expected in the contract (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Target was revised up to 100% from 90% through restructuring in March 2013

this indicator related to productive infrastructure and not bridges; hence, it captures all sub-projects that include productiveinfrastructure (33); of the 33 with contract, 27 were implemented on time, according to contract

title.narrative: At least 25% of project ideas identified in the Municipal Development Plans have budget in the POAs of local governments (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved and surpassed. Revised through restructuring in March 2013

title.narrative: 80% of project beneficiaries are indigenous (original indicator)

comment.narrative: Target has been surpassed.

title.narrative: Increase of total sales of the rural productive supply chain partnerships with US$35 million during the project period (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: This target was revised down to US$35 million (from US$50 million) through restructuring in March 2013
Reflects sales from 189 sub-projects; only sub-projects were considered (and not plans for capacity strengthening)

title.narrative: Sub-project implementation complies with at least 70% of environmental mitigation measures as defined in the business plan (revisedindicator)

comment.narrative: revised through restructuring in March 2013
137 sub-projects complies with 70 to 100% of the mitigation measures (representing 72% of all sub-projects); the rest apply somemitigation measure, but there is no clear progress measure

title.narrative: At least 25% of municipal projects stem from the participatory planning process (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: This target was revised up to 25% (from 5%) through restructuring in March 2013
This indicator has consistently exceeded the original target value of 5%, which was increased to 25%

title.narrative: All financed projects have an environmental management tool developed according to the norms of he Ministry of Environment and Natural Resources, before their implementation (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved;revised through restructuring in March 2013
all sub-projects have an env. management tool

title.narrative: At least 80% of the technical assistance provided to producer organizations is done so in the prevailing language of the participating producer organization (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved;revised through restructuring in March 2013

title.narrative: At least 33% of departments covered by the project have departmental development plans (revised indicator)

comment.narrative: Target has been achieved and exceeded. Revised through restructuring in March 2013
33% corresponds to 7 DDPs; now these exist for 20 DDPs, which is equivalent to 94%
